{# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   /calculators — Pathway A v1: tools gallery

   Restructured from a 5-tile text-list into a polished gallery that
   functions as the canonical entry point for every interactive tool
   on the site. JM's framing: 'each tile shows an actual live
   thumbnail of the tool's heart (mini heatmap, mini chart, mini
   retirement curve…) with an Open button.' This v1 ships the
   gallery structure plus ONE live preview (the heatmap, as the
   showcase proof-of-concept). Other tiles use polished SVG
   illustrations; subsequent iterations can promote them to live
   renders one at a time.

   Hierarchy:
   - Featured row (2 tiles, large): Heatmap (live) + BvSM (chart-SVG)
   - Tools grid (10 tiles, 3-col on desktop): all other Numbers-tier
     interactive tools + the two Arguments-tier interactive ones
     (Half-Life, Melting Ice Cube). The Calculators page becomes the
     comprehensive tools surface; the previous footer 'nav-hint'
     directing readers to The Numbers / The Arguments for the rest
     becomes obsolete since everything's right here.

   Includes previously-missing tools: /heatmap and
   /bitcoin-vs-the-stock-market (calculator section). Both were
   linked elsewhere on the site but didn't appear on this hub.

   Notes for future iterations:
   - Live preview pattern is established by #mini-heatmap →
     calculators-minis.js → renderMiniHeatmap. Adding more live
     previews (mini-bvsm-chart, mini-retirement-curve, mini-power-
     law-channel, etc.) follows the same shape: add a target div
     in the tile markup, write a renderer in calculators-minis.js.
   - SP500_TR_DATA is duplicated between calculators-minis.js and
     bitcoin-vs-the-stock-market.js. Marked 'TR-SYNC' in both
     files. Future cleanup: extract to shared/comparator-data.js.
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ #}

